Narrator

The thump of airplane wheels on asphalt jolted me from my sleep.

Narrator

I was seated in the commercial jet we'd chartered for our royal visit to Thornbough. It had been a long, bumpy ride.

Narrator

As we descended the airplane stairs onto the tarmac, a horn quartet played a jubilant fanfare. Photographers in a cordoned-off press area eagerly began snapping pictures.

Player_Romus_Italic

I shook my sister-in-law's hand. She rapidly withdrew it.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Romus, Your Majesty. You've gotten yourself into quite the mess."

Player_Romus

"It's almost a good thing your sister didn't live to see these times."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Yes, well, fear not."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"That is the idea."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"It will only be under control once you have won."

Player_Romus

"I'm looking forward to your legendary Rumburgian hospitality."

Player_Romus

"Nothing Rumburg can't get me out of."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"We will see about that."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I was not only speaking about Pales."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Please refrain from such attempts at 'comedy'."

Player_Romus

"Indeed, Your Excellency. How have you been?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I have been better. As have you."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"A pity she could not be here."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"How lovely. A pity she could not be here."

Player_Romus

"We'll have to make this a quick visit, I'm afraid. Turbulent times back home."

Narrator

She raised an eyebrow.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Really? From where I'm sitting, your reign looks smooth as silk."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"If that was a joke, it's not very amusing."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Surely you are being facetious. So much has changed."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Hrm, yes. Poetic."

Narrator

I had just finished getting dressed when Lucita entered the compartment. She was outfitted in full military regalia.

Narrator

I was in the bedroom of my royal jet, {RiziaDLCText.RoyalJet}. It had been a long but smooth flight to Thornbourgh.

Narrator

I had just finished getting dressed when I heard a knock on the door to my compartment.

Lucita Azaro

"Your Majesty? Are you decent?"

Player_Romus

"Decent, no. Dressed, yes."

Player_Romus

"You may enter."

Player_Romus

"Ready to meet my sister-in-law?"

Narrator

She sat next to me on the bed and squeezed my hand.

Narrator

He came in and bowed.

Narrator

Lucita was in the seat next to mine. On seeing I was awake, she squeezed my hand surreptitiously.

Player_Romus

"It wasn't easy. I've been nervous about today's meeting."

Player_Romus

"I was having the most marvelous dream. I think you were involved."

Laurento Esquibel

"Ah. Your father was the same way. Restless till the end."

Narrator

He pulled a tin of wax out of his pocket and dabbed some onto the ends of his moustache.

Laurento Esquibel

"Just making sure you're ready for our meeting with your sister-in-law."

Lucita Azaro

"As long as ATO doesn't get involved."

Lucita Azaro

"I'm sure she appreciates that."

Lucita Azaro

"We all do."

Player_Romus

"Is that so? What did I do?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Why, of course. A noblewoman *and* a decorated military officer? You're a credit to our sex."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Let's not delay. We have a full program of events planned at the Emerald Palace."

Player_Romus

"It would be an honor to ride with you."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Let's not delay. We have a full program of events planned at the Emerald Palace."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I was not only speaking about Pales."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Splendid."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Frankly, given the state of things between our kingdoms, I ought to leave you high and dry."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Need I remind you of your kingdom's broken energy promises?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"What were you thinking when you took advantage of our embargo on Wehzek oil to begin importing it yourself?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"But we share a common goal. The rescue of dear Princess Vina from her Palesian captors."

Player_Romus

"What transgressions?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I should say so. I needn't remind you of the superiority of Rumburg's military technology."

Narrator

She drew herself back.

Narrator

Lucita smoothly cut in.

Player_Romus

"The capture of the gas field is less important to me than the eradication of Western influence."

Lucita Azaro

"Actually, Your Excellency, the capabilities of the Rizian military have grown by leaps and bounds since the beginning of King Romus' reign."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"We shall prepare a sizeable shipment of our very finest equipment. KA-74s, grenades, body armor... all will be at your disposal."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"It is the least I can do."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I expect you to use it responsibly."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Hmm. I thought you might."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"That is it."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"What else do you need to win the war?"

Player_Romus

"We could use more tanks. Our men on the ground are moving around unprotected."

Player_Romus

"Is there anything experimental you're working on? Something the enemy won't expect at all?"

Player_Romus

"We need trucks. All that equipment is no good if we can't transport it."

Narrator

She put a hand to her necklace.

Narrator

A confidential glint appeared in her eye.

Player_Romus

"Oh, God. No, we don't want any part in that."

Player_Romus

"The Palesians hardly qualify as human. But yes, we'll take it."

Narrator

Lucita peered at her closely.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"That can most certainly be arranged."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Now. Please let me know if you have any serious requests."

Narrator

I saw Lucita nod in approval.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Here's the rub, though."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"And furthermore, Rizia's continued ties to Sordland irk me to no end."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Do you understand what I want from you, Your Majesty?"

Narrator

She raised an eyebrow.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Promise to leave the Bluds alone, and I will consider offering you additional assistance."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I do have one rather unconventional suggestion."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"You could sell us your Port of Monqiz."

Player_Romus

"We'll sell you our largest port over my dead body."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Your efforts to modernize the port have been admirable, but with our technology, we can maximize its efficiency even further."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"You wouldn't be losing Monqiz. You'd be sharing it."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"As you're shipping us a sizeable amount of energy through Monqiz, it's only logical to give us a say in how that shipping is run."

Player_Romus

"Such a cooperation would truly cement the alliance between our monarchies."

Player_Romus

"If we did this for you, we'd never owe you anything again."

Player_Romus

"We are trying to become less dependent on Rumburg. This will accomplish the opposite."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Less dependent on everything but our military aid, you mean."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Let's not beat around the bush. You have come here to ask for help in the war against Pales."

Player_Romus

"That'd be convenient for you, wouldn't it? But no, RIzia is well on its way to defeating Pales on its own."

Narrator

Lucita nodded proudly in confirmation.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Is that so? How marvelous."

Player_Romus

"Really, there is no need."

Player_Romus

"Thank you, Your Excellency. Your affection for Vina is touching."

Narrator

Lucita nodded proudly in confirmation.

Narrator

Lucita shook her head worriedly.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Is that so? How dreadful."

Player_Romus

"Well... maybe just in case."

Player_Romus

"I do not need Rumburg or anyone's help. The Lord has ordained that we shall win this fight."

Narrator

Lucita bit her lip.

Player_Romus

"Simply put, we're screwed without you.

Narrator

Lucita winced.

Player_Romus

"No. Of course I will let you know if the situation changes."

Narrator

Beatrice smirked.

Player_Romus

"Yes, fine. Perhaps we do require Rumburg's assistance after all."

Player_Romus

"A temporary setback. I am certain we will recover."

Player_Romus

"Absolutely not. I am a king of my word, and I stick to my agreements."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"No need for hyperbole. But it would be quite the grand gesture."

Narrator

Beatrice sighed in disappointment.

Player_Romus

"All right. Here's what I am willing to do."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Yes?"

Player_Romus

"I will allow the Bludish people into Rizia once more."

Player_Romus

"I will cease Rizia's participation in Operation Bear Trap."

Player_Romus

"I will end Rizia's trade deal with Sordland."

Player_Romus

"I will nationalize the Sordish resort in Valenqiris."

Player_Romus

"I will break off the bonds Rizia purchased from Sordland."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I understand the need to remain invested in Gasom. But outside of that, I don't see why you should be doing the Sords any favors."

Narrator

The Queen nodded with some satisfaction.

Lucita Azaro

"I sincerely hope your technology lives up to its reputation."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Anything else?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"My generosity stops there, I am afraid."

Player_Romus

"I understand. You're doing enough for us."

Player_Romus

"But I wasn't finished with my requests. Can Rizia sweeten the deal somehow?"

Player_Romus

"We need manpower. Can you send soldiers?"

Narrator

Beatrics closed her eyes and shook her head.

Player_Romus

"I love all Golcondists. And they love me."

Player_Romus

"Be not quick to judge your fellow man. Especially when he walks in the path of righteousness."

Player_Romus

"The Bludish Freedom Front? You mean the terrorist organization?"

Lucita Azaro

"Additional Golcondist support would work wonders for their morale, I am sure."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"They make strange bedfellows. But useful ones."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"That depends, Your Majesty. How flexible are you willing to be?"

Player_Romus

"Actually, forget it. I refuse to budge."

Player_Romus

"You win. I will sell you the Monqiz port after all."

Lucita Azaro

"More than enough. Really."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Well... remember what I asked you about the port of Monqiz?"

Player_Romus

"My answer is still no."

Player_Romus

"Fine, Your Excellency. I will sell you our largest port in exchange for more war support."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"We will have to agree to disagree about the Bluds' righteousness. But they can be useful allies."

Player_Romus

"Nonetheless, this isn't what I had in mind. I kindly refuse the offer."

Narrator

As soon as we were in motion, Beatrice's cordial expression gave way to an icy stare.

Player_Romus

"Your Majesty, what exactly is Rumburg's trouble with Sordland?"

Player_Romus

"In case you haven't forgotten, our investment in Sordish gas is benefiting both of our kingdoms."

Player_Romus

"I'm not a fan of the Sords either. Not after the trouble they've been giving you."

Player_Romus

"I cannot break my agreement with Wiktor Smolak. The fate of Zille hangs in the balance."

Player_Romus

"We are oppressing no one. We are merely executing counterterrorism measures."

Player_Romus

"I did not realize Rumburg and the BFF were that closely connected."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Don't think I haven't noticed your attempts to cozy up to other nations..."

Player_Romus

"I don't care about my standing with GRACE."

Player_Romus

"What can I do to get back in your good graces? Pun intended."

Player_Romus

"Please, Beatrice. I'll do anything."

Player_Romus

"We'll sell you our largest port over my dead body."

Player_Romus

"Sure, why not? I don't see the harm in it."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Until you take Pales, that is."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Look at how shabby the port has become. With our technology, we can get it into tip-top shape in an instant."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Your efforts to modernize the port have been admirable, but with our technology, we can maximize its efficiency even further."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Don't be so pessimistic, Your Grace. I foresee advantages for both of us."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"You wouldn't be losing Monqiz. You'd be sharing it."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"As you're shipping us a sizeable amount of energy through Monqiz, it's only logical to give us a say in how that shipping is run."

Player_Romus

"I can see the sense of what you're saying. But I still think the disadvantages outweigh the benefits."

Player_Romus

"Such a cooperation would truly cement the alliance between our monarchies."

Player_Romus

"If we did this for you, we'd never owe you anything again."

Player_Romus

"We are trying to become less dependent on Rumburg. This will accomplish the opposite."

Player_Romus

"I know it's a risk, but victory will be worth it. Rumburg may purchase the port, Your Excellency."

Lucita Azaro

"I sincerely hope your weaponry lives up to its reputation."

Player_Romus

"Not so fast. I think I deserve a little more than that."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"You drive a hard bargain, Your Grace."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"What else do you want?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"You will continue to receive the support of GRACE. That is enough of a reward."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"You drive a hard bargain, Your Majesty."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I do still respect you, Your Majesty. But know that you are on thin ice. With me, and with the other monarchs of this world."

Narrator

Beatrice smiled warmly.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Let's not beat around the bush, Your Majesty."

Player_Romus

"Rumburg helped carry Rizia through the tough years after the uprising. I am forever grateful for that. But I have begun to rethink our partnership."

Player_Romus

"You're bluffing, Your Excellency. You need Rizia as much as we need you."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I don't believe you're joking."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Rethink? You are turning your back on Rumburg completely."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I wish I could believe they were merely mistakes."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"You ceded control of your kingdom's parliament to a bunch of scheming reformists..."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"What were you thinking when you took advantage of our embargo on Wehzek oil to begin importing it yourself?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"As if that weren't enough, you arrested your own cousin and brought disgrace upon your royal house!"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"The treatment of Dastnurists in your country is an insult to us."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"You ceded control of your kingdom's parliament to a bunch of scheming reformists..."

Narrator

She breathed in deeply.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I have to ask. Do our blood ties mean nothing to you?"

Player_Romus

"Your sister and I were forced into an unhappy marriage. What you call blood ties, I call shackles."

Player_Romus

"Don't be ridiculous, Beatrice. You're like the sister I never had. And I know how fond you are of Vina."

Player_Romus

"Please don't cut us off, Your Excellency. Innocent citizens will suffer."

Narrator

Laurento tentatively spoke up.

Narrator

Her eyes momentarily softened.

Narrator

Beatrice's nostrils flared.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Or of our joint investment in the Sordish gas industry?"

Narrator

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Besides which... surely you see the economic benefits of staying in GRACE?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Your citizens are suffering as it is. We've played no part in that."

Narrator

Her nostrils flared.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Hmm. I am glad you see the wisdom of staying in GRACE."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"But I am glad you see the wisdom of staying in GRACE."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"There is one thing you can do that will dramatically improve your standing with us. I warn you it is rather unorthodox."

Player_Romus

"We have other partnerships now. Rumburg simply isn't as important to us anymore."

Player_Romus

"If there's something you want from Rizia, please just spit it out."

Player_Romus

"I'll bite. How can you help us?"

Player_Romus

"We accepted your help already. Nothing came of it."

Player_Romus

"So what will it take to stay in your good graces? No pun intended."

Player_Romus

"So what will it take to stay in your good graces? Pun intended."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Well, since you've mentioned it... I do have one suggestion. I warn you it is rather unorthodox."

"His Majesty is being hyperbolic. But you must understand the risks inherent in such a sale, Your Excellency."

"We'll sell you our largest port over my dead body."

Player_Romus

Player_Romus

"Granting your kingdom a foothold in the southern Antacean. I see."

Player_Romus

"I have some concerns about that proposal. To put it mildly."

"As you should, Your Majesty. Giving away another part of Rizia before Zille is returned would be most unwise."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Risks? I see nothing but rewards for both of us."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Anything worth doing in life involves risk, Mr. Esquibel."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Don't be so pessimistic, Your Grace. I foresee advantages for both of us."

"Indeed it would."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"As would any king. Perhaps Mr. Esquibel can help you see past them."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I agree it would be quite the grand gesture."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"We have certain contacts within Wehlen who could stir up trouble in Zille. Possibly enough to overthrow the government."

Narrator

Laurento's eyes grew wide.

Player_Romus

"All right, Your Excellency. How do I recommit?"

Laurento Esquibel

"What His Majesty means to say is--"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I know perfectly well what His Majesty means to say."

Narrator

Our limousine screeched to a halt in the middle of the empty freeway. I heard the squeal of tires as the rest of the motorcade did the same.

Player_Romus

"Good day, Your Excellency."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Oh?"

Player_Romus

"Forget it. That sounds like a spectacularly bad idea."

Player_Romus

"I don't know about Zille, but I do care about our economic partnership. How do we restore that?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Don't think of it as dependence. Think of it as venturing into the future together."

Laurento Esquibel

"Were your security councilor here today, she would tell you the same thing. Using stronger language."

Player_Romus

"I agree with you -- and with House Azaro. Your Excellency, there is no way I can sell the port."

Narrator

Laurento breathed a sigh of relief.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"But I simply cannot abide by the terms of the agreement you made with Wehlen."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Rumburg has been working hard to assist the Bludish Freedom Front in their struggle for liberation. It does us no good for you to be aiding in their oppression."

Player_Romus

"Your Excellency, I assure you our partnership with Rumburg is more valuable to us than our foreign connections."

Player_Romus

"No, I'm not sure that I do."

"Then I kindly ask you to prove it."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"And furthermore, Rizia's continued ties to Sordland irk me to no end."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Do you understand what I want from you, Your Majesty?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Break at least one of your agreements with Wehlen or Sordland, and your partnership with Rumburg and GRACE will continue as normal."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Stop associating with the Sords, and your partnership with Rumburg and GRACE will continue as normal."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Absolutely not. I am a king of my word, and I stick to my agreements."

Player_Romus

"I will not. The heretic Golcondists do not deserve my mercy."

"Strong words, Your Majesty."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I'll put it in plain terms."

"I will break off the bonds Rizia purchased from Sordland."

"Actually, never mind. I refuse to budge."

"I will allow the Bludish people into Rizia once more."

"I will cease Rizia's participation in Operation Bear Trap."

Player_Romus

"I will end Rizia's trade deal with Sordland."

Player_Romus

"I will nationalize the Sordish resort in Valenqiris."

Player_Romus

"I do. But I've worked hard to cultivate our international partnerships. I will not break them just to appease you."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I understand the need to remain invested in Gasom. But outside of that, I don't see why you should be doing the Sords any favors."

"In case you haven't forgotten, our investment in Sordish gas is benefiting both of our kingdoms."

"You may consider yourself out of the danger zone as far as GRACE is concerned."

Player_Romus

"All right. Here's what I am willing to do."

"Do not fool yourself."

"Not officially, of course. You will find no paper trail."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I do have one other suggestion. But I warn you it is rather unorthodox."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"A pity, Your Majesty. Truly saddening."

"The Bluds? But they're terrorists."

Player_Romus

"Those Golcondists? Never."

Player_Romus

"That's it? Of course I welcome the opportunity to assist devout Wruhecists in need."

Player_Romus

"Hmm. Is that how you help us get Zille back, then?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"If you wish."

Laurento Esquibel

"As loathe as I am to suggest violence as a solution to the Zille conundrum...  an internal resistance effort from the BFF could work in perfect concert with the Derdian mercenaries already present in the region."

Laurento Esquibel

"I am still loathe to suggest violence as a solution to the Zille conundrum. But in the absence of an agreement with President Smolak, an internal resistance might be our last hope."

Laurento Esquibel

"I am loathe to suggest violence as a solution to the Zille conundrum. Especially since Wehlen may yet return the region through diplomatic means."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"They are a persecuted minority fighting an oppressive government."

Narrator

Laurento coughed.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Try to see past their religion and empathize with their struggle against the Wehzek government."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"A struggle that can, conveniently, be channeled towards Zille."

Player_Romus

"I don't want the BFF getting in the way of our existing resistance plans."

Player_Romus

"The BFF would be active in Zille sooner or later, anyway. We'd just be giving them a nudge."

Player_Romus

"The BFF have their own fight going on. I don't want to interfere with it one way or another."

Player_Romus

"If we funded the BFF and Smolak found out about it, he'd have an excuse to hold on to Zille forever."

Player_Romus

"Why do I get the feeling you're trying to use both Rizia and the BFF toward your own ends, Your Excellency?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Don't be so cynical. I am giving you a final chance to prove that your interests still align with ours."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"And who would tell him? Do you run that leaky of a ship, Your Majesty?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Exactly."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"That makes sense. But a monetary contribution towards their struggle would nonetheless be greatly appreciated."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I am giving you a final chance to prove that your interests align with ours. You may take it or leave it."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"What a shame."

Player_Romus

"Good thing it's just us then, isn't it? I agree to sell the Port of Monqiz to Rumburg."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"You may consider your status with GRACE restored. And then some."

Narrator

Beatrice frowned.

Player_Romus

"However, I'm willing to do what we talked about earlier."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"I am afraid I see no other way for Rizia to redeem itself."

Narrator

Laurento tried to hide his dismay.

Player_Romus

"I'll co-fund the Bludish Freedom Front along with Rumburg, but I fully expect them to be of assistance in Zille."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Of course. That's perfectly fine."

Player_Romus

"No... I don't like this. Is there something else I can do for Rumburg instead?"

Player_Romus

"I'd love to agree to this. But I don't have the budget for it."

Player_Romus

"You don't have to twist my arm, Your Excellency. I'll fund the Bludish Freedom Front, if you can promise me they'll help us 'liberate' Zille."

She clasped her hands together.

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Well..."

Beatrice Livingston (R)

"Oh, my."

"I'll go in on funding the BFF. But tell your contacts there to stick to northern Wehlen."

"Zealotry? I am telling the objective truth. If you could only look beyond the narrow worldview of St. Dast, you'd understand."

"Up to this point, we have been aiding the Bluds' liberation efforts in the north of Wehlen. But I see no reason why their struggle can't be directed southward as well."

"If I may, Your Excellency... Zille has nothing to do with the former Greater Bludia region. Why would the BFF get involved there?"

Beatrice Livingston (R)
